race.comment: CULLEN SKINK (1) is a former Clarken galloper who had first run for the new yard last time over further and was safely held. Freshened and will relish this easier company. Well back in trip but will storm home late. OUR DIVINYL (5) hasn't been going too badly in tougher company lately. Looks very well placed this line-up and if fronts here (also entered for town Saturday) would go close on best figures. LAVA LAD (7) got back into winning form last time at Lock. Has got a bit of a fitness edge on most of the others and in winning form can run well again. SIR PANAMA (2) resumes from a long break for a new yard. Has a good record here though and likely to play a major role. STARDEALT (3) is a former Victorian who has been racing over further but well placed this level and is worth including.
